Name Rascal/Expressions/Values/List/StrictSubList

Syntax Exp1 < Exp2
Types
Exp1 Exp2 Exp1 < Exp2
list[T1] list[T2] bool
Description Yields true if the value of Exp1 is a strict sublist of the value of Exp2, and false otherwise.
Examples 
rascal>[1, 2, 3] < [1, 2, 3, 4];
bool: true
rascal>[1, 2, 3, 4] < [1, 2, 3, 4];
bool: false
rascal>[1, 3, 5] < [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
bool: true
Questions
